data.title: Moyles and Searle get provincial call ups
data.meta_description: Navan RFC Senior Women's player Rosie Searle has been named by the Connacht Women management team in their 38-player squad for the 2024 Vodafone Women’s Interprovincial Championship, which kicks off this weekend.
data.text:
Navan RFC Senior Women's player Rosie Searle has been named by the Connacht Women management team in their 38-player squad for the 2024 Vodafone Women’s Interprovincial Championship, which kicks off this weekend.

Searle who studies in Galway University was not only part of our Women's 1st XV squad which won a Leinster League Division 3 & Paul Cusack Cup double last season, but she also took part in the IRFU's University 7's tournament held last spring with Galway University.

The Connacht Women's team begin their interpro campaign on Saturday away to Leinster at Energia Park (KO 4:45pm).

ABBEY MOYLES

Former Navan RFC Youths Player Abby Moyles has been named by Ulster Senior Women's Head Coach, Murray Houston in their squad for the upcoming 2024/25 Vodafone Women’s Interprovincial Championship.

This is the second year of Moyles involvement in the Ulster Senior Women's team and follows on from their involvement on the "Wolfhounds" (Leinster/Ulster) team that completed in last years Celtic Challenge competition and also being in the inaugural Irish Women's Under 20 squad.
